criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Healthy, living independently and self-reported;

          -  Aged ≥ 65 years;

          -  Having the ability to understand the study procedures.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Being obese (BMI > 30 kg/m2);

          -  Smoking more than 10 cigarettes a day;

          -  Having a disease such as cardiovascular disease and other chronic diseases (diabetes,
             thyroid disorders, cancer, heart, lung and kidney disease;

          -  Taking medications known to influence appetite, food intake or body weight in the past
             three months;

          -  Changing their diet and exercise in the last 3 months;

          -  Having unexpected weight loss in the last 3 months.
